 The US retiring baby-boomer problem makes it important to pay down the national debt
The problem wasn’t huge when the Baby Boomers were zero to 20, so why when they’re 70 to 90?"
"The relevant number is what’s called the dependency ratio of working people to population.
"Any fiscal problem that might arise in caring for the elderly "boomers" has already been paid for, by the payroll tax rise of 1983, designed for this purpose."
